### ─── AUTH ROUTES ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### POST /api/v2/users/login     — login and receive HttpOnly cookie
### GET  /api/v2/users/auth/me   — check session (requires cookie)
### POST /api/v2/users/auth/logout — clear cookie

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3002/api/v2/users

# ─── UPDATE THESE to match a real user in your MongoDB ────────────────────────
@validEmail    = charlie7@example.com
@validPassword = password123


### ── 1. LOGIN — success ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "{{validEmail}}",
    "password": "{{validPassword}}"
}


### ── 2. LOGIN — missing credentials (expect 400) ────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "{{validEmail}}"
}


### ── 3. LOGIN — wrong password (expect 400) ─────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "{{validEmail}}",
    "password": "wrongpassword"
}


### ── 4. LOGIN — user not found (expect 400) ─────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "doesnotexist@example.com",
    "password": "password123"
}


### ── 5. CHECK SESSION — success (run AFTER login, cookie auto-sent) ─────────
### The REST Client stores the Set-Cookie header from request #1 automatically.
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me


### ── 6. CHECK SESSION — no token (expect 401) ───────────────────────────────
### Send request with an empty/invalid cookie to simulate a missing session.
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Cookie: accessToken=


### ── 7. CHECK SESSION — expired/invalid token (expect 500 → JWT error) ──────
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Cookie: accessToken=this.is.not.a.valid.jwt


### ── 8. LOGOUT — success ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout


### ── 9. CHECK SESSION after logout — expect 401 ─────────────────────────────
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
